From ebea2f5c7073ae57aef0b6aff6a094469dad75a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kannan Saravanan <kannsara@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2025 15:38:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] QSDK: Platform: wifi:ath12k: Add support for MLO reconfig
 QMI message

This patch introduces a new QMI message, QMI_MLO_RECONFIG (0x005F),
to update the adjacency information of targets to the firmware when
a target is bypassed or brought back from the bypassed state.

It also adds the corresponding request and response handlers for
this message.

To support both the maximum capabilities in the Host Capability QMI
message and the bypass configuration in the MLO Reconfig QMI message
during SSR scenarios, we need to maintain two instances of WSI
information.

Introduce bypass_wsi_info to store and use the WSI data specifically
for bypass cases.

Patch-dependency:
	0325-02-wifi-ath12k-Add-support-for-four-link-MLO-in-AP-MLD.patch
